{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958624,"nonce":"Bm4ZlT6GRHj66xi/sczngo/Db0c=","kind":"spec","title":"kref local-file tracking — B3: drift visibility — design","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958624,"nonce":"YvcEyVZZ5fPyfa/M4zAmu2eMxGA=","body":"# kref local-file tracking — B3: drift visibility — design\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-26\n**Status:** IMPLEMENTED on `main` (commits `6f2bceb` engine, `cf0615c` CLI).\nNote: `list --check` renders a drift summary section, not an in-table column.\n**Scope:** Show whether a tracked file has diverged from its entry. Presentation\nonly — no new persisted state. Builds on B1 (tracking) and the B2 reconcile\nengine. Write-back (B4) is still out of scope.\n\n## 1. Key idea — no new storage\n\nThe entry's stored `Body` already *is* the last-synced content, so drift is a\nlive compare: a tracked entry is `drifted` when its file's body (trailer\nstripped) or title differs from the entry, `in-sync` when equal, `missing` when\nnothing is at `TrackedPath`. No hash field, no new op. (A stored hash would only\nadd *entry-side* drift, which is a B4 concern.)\n\n## 2. Surfaces\n\n- **`show`** (human): for a tracked entry, add a line\n  `Tracked: \u003cpath\u003e [in-sync|drifted|missing]`.\n- **`list --check`**: add a drift marker per tracked entry; reads each tracked\n  file **only** under `--check`, so bare `list` stays fast.\n- **`kref reconcile --dry-run [--json]`**: report what *would* sync without\n  mutating (no store writes, no confirm prompt). This is the **single machine\n  interface** for drift; `show --json` and `list --json` therefore keep their\n  current snapshot shapes (non-breaking).\n\n`missing` in `show`/`list` means \"not at the tracked path\" — display does **not**\nself-heal moved files (that is a per-entry repo walk); `reconcile` is where a\nmove is detected and re-pointed.\n\n## 3. Mechanism\n\n- **`bridge.DriftState(s, snap) (string, error)`** — read-only: `missing` if the\n  file is absent; else compare stripped body + derived title to the entry →\n  `in-sync` | `drifted`. No secret scan (display never pulls).\n- **`--dry-run`** threads a `dryRun bool` through `ReconcileEntry`/`Reconcile`:\n  it does the full read + secret scan + compare (so a secret still surfaces as\n  `error`, and a move as `relocated`) but **skips the mutations** (`Store.Update`,\n  `RecordOrigin`, `Store.Track`). Dry-run bulk runs read-only, so it skips the\n  confirm prompt. Dry-run action map: `synced` = would-sync (drifted),\n  `unchanged` = in-sync, `relocated` = would-relocate, `missing`, `ambiguous`,\n  `error` = would fail closed on a secret.\n\n## 4. Slices (TDD)\n\nA. **Engine:** `bridge.DriftState`; thread `dryRun` through\n   `ReconcileEntry`/`Reconcile` (guard the mutating calls; update existing call\n   sites). Tests: drift states (in-sync/drifted/missing); dry-run reports the\n   right action and does **not** mutate the entry.\nB. **CLI:** `show` drift line; `list --check` marker; `reconcile --dry-run`\n   (no prompt, no writes). Tests for each.\n\n## 5. Testing\n\n- `internal/bridge`: `DriftState` returns in-sync/drifted/missing; a dry-run\n  `Reconcile` of a drifted file returns `synced` yet leaves `entry.Body`\n  unchanged; dry-run of a moved file returns `relocated` without re-pointing\n  `TrackedPath`.\n- `cmd/kref`: `show` of a drifted tracked entry prints `drifted`; `list --check`\n  marks it (bare `list` does not read files); `reconcile --dry-run` reports the\n  drifted set and changes nothing (`show` still shows the old body afterward).\n\n## 6. Out of scope\n\n- **B4** write-back (entry → file) with a `git merge-file` conflict model."}]}